<h3>Center on the x &amp; y axes.</h3>
<p>No need to determine the height of the element or the container. Uses css transform &amp; position.

<div class='grid example'>

  <div class='column-6'>
    <div class='box center'></div>
  </div>

  <div class='column-6'>
<pre class='language-css'><code>.box {
  #center > .xy();
}

// css output
.box {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  -webkit-transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-50%);
  -ms-transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-50%);
  transform: translateX(-50%) translateY(-50%);
}
</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>


<h3>Center on a specific axis (y only).</h3>

<div class='grid example'>

  <div class='column-6'>
    <div class='box center-y'></div>
  </div>

  <div class='column-6'>
<pre class='language-css'><code>.box {
  #center > .y();
}

// css output
.box {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  -webkit-transform: translateY(-50%);
  -ms-transform: translateY(-50%);
  transform: translateY(-50%);
}
</code></pre>
  </div>
</div>

